The paper deals with the problem of constructing planar drawings with few bends for partially embedded graphs and simultaneously planar graphs. This involves combinatorial embedding, graph theory, and algorithms for planar graph drawing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves the use of data structures and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely categories. The paper also deals with graph theory and planarity, which suggests cs.GT (Graph Theory) as a likely category. Finally, the paper discusses efficient algorithms, which suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible category.
